ProtoResult:
. "Suppose there's an integer $N$ such that $a_n\ne0$ if $n\ge
   N$ and $$ \lim_{n\to\infty}\left|a_{n+1}\over a_n\right|=L, 
   $$ where $0\le L\le\infty$ Then the radius of convergence of
   $\sum_{n=0}^\infty a_n(x-x_0)^n$ is $R=1/ L$ which should be
   interpreted to mean that $R=0$ if $L=\infty$ or $R=\infty$ 
   if $L=0$"
